bug.short_desc: Compiler Crash when building for low cost Skylake
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1181758 Full logs of compile
building fdk-aac on Fedora24 crashes when using a low-cost Skylake (Celeron G3900). As described on the gmp-mailinglist (https://gmplib.org/list-archives/gmp-bugs/2016-July/003978.html) the problem would be fixed when updating GMP to 6.1.1.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): gcc version 6.1.1 20160621 (Red Hat 6.1.1-3) (GCC) gmp-6.1.0-2.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible: always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. git clone https://github.com/mstorsjo/fdk-aac 2. cd fdk-aac 3. ./autogen.sh 4. ./configure 5. make
Actual results: CXX libAACdec/src/aacdec_drc.lo libAACdec/src/aacdec_drc.cpp:137:3: internal compiler error: Illegal instruction pParams->cut = FL2FXCONST_DBL(0.0f); ^~~~~~~ Please submit a full bug report, with preprocessed source if appropriate. See <http://bugzilla.redhat.com/bugzilla> for instructions. Preprocessed source stored into /tmp/ccx49K6D.out file, please attach this to your bugreport. Makefile:1264: recipe for target 'libAACdec/src/aacdec_drc.lo' failed make: *** [libAACdec/src/aacdec_drc.lo] Error 1 [0.14] molli123@revo:~/fdk-aac >
Expected results: compile as it does on older systems
Linux revo.fritz.box 4.6.3-300.fc24.x86_64 #1 SMP Fri Jun 24 20:52:41 UTC 2016 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux
